id: pmc-t7ie
title: Production readiness refresh for pm-changelog v2026.05.23-7
description: "Govern the full continuation pass requested on 2026-05-24 local time, including official pm SDK compliance, TypeScript-only source and tests, documentation restructuring, GitHub/npm/dependency checks, temp install verification, changelog self-generation, secret-history review, commit, push, npm publication, and public GitHub release verification."
type: Epic
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[3]: governance,production,release
created_at: "2026-05-23T22:14:06.441Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-23T22:18:43.118Z"
deadline: "2026-05-24T00:00:00.000Z"
author: codex
estimated_minutes: 180
acceptance_criteria: "- Source and test authoring uses strongly typed TypeScript and the official @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk surface.\\n- README is minimal and detailed docs live under docs/ with linked progressive-disclosure navigation.\\n- GitHub issues, PRs, Actions, Dependabot alerts, npm outdated, and npm audit are checked with gh/npm.\\n- Release workflow remains enabled for daily NPM/GitHub release only when changes exist.\\n- Clean temporary pm installs pass for local and published package sources.\\n- Git history scan finds no confirmed private data.\\n- CHANGELOG.md is regenerated by pm-changelog from closed pm items.\\n- Changes are committed, pushed, published to npm, and released publicly on GitHub."
reviewer: steve
risk: high
confidence: high
sprint: 2026-05-release
release: v2026.05.23-7
resolution: "Completed the v2026.05.23-7 production readiness refresh with official SDK compliance, TypeScript-only authored tests, progressive docs, GitHub/npm/security checks, release gate verification, and clean local pm install evidence."
expected_result: "pm-changelog is release-ready with strongly typed TypeScript source and tests, official pm SDK usage, complete docs, clean verification evidence, regenerated changelog output, and automated npm/GitHub release readiness."
actual_result: "Source now uses direct @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk imports without local shims. Test source is TypeScript and compiles through tsconfig.test.json. README is minimal and docs pages hold usage, release, and development details. GitHub checks found no open issues or pull requests and no Dependabot alerts. npm checks found no outdated packages and zero production vulnerabilities. npm run release:check passed with 18 tests. Local temp pm install activated the extension and generated a smoke changelog. History scan found no confirmed private data. Final changelog generation, commit, push, workflow release, npm publication, and published install verification proceed from this closed epic."
